      didYouKnow: `The U.S. government's interest payments on the national debt exceeded $1 trillion annually for the first time in 2024 — more than the entire federal defence budget. As real interest rates rise with large deficits, debt service costs consume an ever-larger share of the federal budget, leaving less room for discretionary spending. This is the long-run fiscal consequence of the crowding-out mechanism the AP loanable funds model illustrates.`,
