        front: 'Why might automatic stabilisers be preferred to discretionary fiscal policy for business cycle management?',
        back: 'Automatic stabilisers (progressive income taxes, unemployment insurance) respond immediately to economic conditions without legislative action — eliminating the inside lag entirely. In a recession, tax revenue automatically falls and transfer payments rise, injecting support into the economy before Congress can act. They also phase out automatically in recoveries, avoiding the over-stimulation risk of poorly timed discretionary policy.',
