        front: 'State the balance of payments identity and explain what it implies about trade deficits.',
        back: 'CA + KA = 0. A current account deficit (imports > exports) must be exactly matched by a capital account surplus (net capital inflows — foreigners invest more in the country than residents invest abroad). A trade deficit is not independently "bad" — it is always financed by foreign willingness to hold the country\'s assets. The U.S. trade deficit reflects global demand for dollar-denominated assets.',
